<paragraph id="8BD33690FFA93312FF6712B9FA8FBC3B" blockId="5.[136,1452,918,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="157">Description:—Cells solitary, radially symmetrical, with conspicuous marginal rimoportulae extending on to valve exterior in hyaline tubes, not reaching centre (annulus), terminating at valve edge in semi-circular slit. Numbers vary, 5–8. Annulus small, central, with rows of loculate puncta situated between marginal rimoportulae. Valves appear dissimilar (compare Figures 22–24, with 25 and 26).</paragraph>
